  "text": "Rather, Shim successfully points out that it is a strategy to stave off the domination of global media giants from America. The move to incorporate some of the elements of American popular culture into Korea's own is actually counterhegemonic towards the Western cultural domination. By adopting Kraidy's notion of 'hybridity', this study view that the social condition of the audience will determine how the process of hybridity will take place. Hence, the reason behind why some scholars notably David [CITATION_1] have urged for a re-examination of the cultural imperialism theory.",
